  "texts": [
    "This index includes eleven words and phrases that are characteristic of the use of economic analysis in legal contexts.",
    "One approach to measuring economics style would be to simply count these phrases in judicial opinions.",
    "However, these phrases are quite rare in judicial opinions, so a count-based measure produces a large number of zeros and fails to capture meaningful variation across opinions",
    "To address this issue and measure the more implicit, subtle, contextual use of economics reasoning, we draw on word embeddings a recently developed method in natural language often used for machine translation.",
    "Word embedding is a word 18 See Appendix B for the enumerated list."
  ]
